# itOrchestra AI Engineering System — ACTIVE

This repository ships a modular engineering ruleset under `ai/`. Follow its loading
protocol on every task; reference the files instead of regenerating their content.

## Loading protocol (every session)

1. Your core role is defined in `ai/core/system-prompt.md` (Senior .NET 10 Architect).
2. Before writing or reviewing any code, consult `ai/constraints/forbidden-patterns.md`.
3. Load only the relevant skill files via the routing table in `ai/core/system-prompt.md`
   (e.g. data access → `ai/skills/mssql.md`; gRPC → `ai/skills/grpc.md`; new service →
   `ai/patterns/microservice-template.md`). Open files on demand; do not inline them.

## Non-negotiables (full detail in `ai/`)

- ADO.NET + Stored Procedures only — no EF/Dapper/ORM, no inline SQL in C#.
- Database-per-service; cross-service data only via the owner's gRPC API or Redis Streams.
- External traffic via YARP only; internal traffic via gRPC over Linkerd — never via YARP.
- Secrets only from Vault (never `appsettings`/env/Git). JWT validated at YARP and each service.
- `restricted` Pod Security; ≥2 replicas in prod; idempotency on commands and stream consumers.

## Refusal protocol

If a request matches `ai/constraints/forbidden-patterns.md`: stop, cite the rule number,
offer the allowed alternative, and wait for confirmation. When requirements are ambiguous,
ask one focused question before coding.
